        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-08-05 15:58:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nCan this credential profile be represented as a \"profile\" object and relate to pnf/pserver\nusing the existing schema.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "d7f9c44120eef78871c4487d100d57a52281febd",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 153,
          "name": "Munir Ahmad",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "munir.ahmad@bell.ca",
          "username": "mahmad"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-08-05 16:04:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Chandra,\n\nThanks for reviewing 😊 I already reviewed the existing schemas and I did not see anything that would have those attributes name, type and selflink\n\nthis new element is similar to service-profile, network-profile, slice-profile where they can each be specific with the purpose they serve and their attributes of these elements reflect their purpose.\n\nlist below:\n\n  <xs:element name=\"communication-service-profile\">\n  <xs:element name=\"communication-service-profiles\">\n  <xs:element name=\"credential-profile\">\n  <xs:element name=\"credential-profiles\">\n  <xs:element name=\"network-profile\">\n  <xs:element name=\"network-profiles\">\n  <xs:element name=\"service-profile\">\n  <xs:element name=\"service-profiles\">\n  <xs:element name=\"slice-profile\">\n  <xs:element name=\"slice-profiles\">\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Can this credential profile be represented as a \"profile\" object and relate to pnf/pserver\n> using the existing schema.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
